						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up on the ghāṭ near the western gate of the Saṅgamēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Heijra 1153, Rudhirōdgāri.</hi></p>						

						<p>It states that Heijra Mahammadu Sāhebulagāru exempted the toll on the pilgrims arriving for an auspicious bath in the river Kṛishnā on the occasion of Kanyā-Bhāgīrathi.</p>						

						</summary>
